HEADWORD: hoagy
<hw>hoagy</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a large
sandwich on a long crusty roll that is split lengthwise and filled with
meats and cheese (and tomato and onion and lettuce and condiments);
different names are used in different sections of the U. S., such as
<altname>hero</altname>, <altname>grinder</altname>, and
<altname>submarine</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bomber, grinder, hero, hero sandwich, hoagie, Cuban
sandwich, Italian sandwich, poor boy, sub, submarine, submarine
sandwich, torpedo, wedge, zep.</syn>⟦br⟧
